Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.52,0:03:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyashirazu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.48,0:03:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:03:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.22,0:04:07.44,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(240, 100)\fad(800,1500)}Sixth Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.22,0:04:07.44,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(240, 370)\fad(800,1500)}Papillon Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.93,0:06:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an4}Sylf, Translator\NNanne, Timing\NCollectr, Editor\NRaziel666 & Robo210, Quality Check\NCollectr, Typesetter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.93,0:06:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want water?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.69,0:06:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got some great stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.94,0:06:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had a lot of soba at street-side stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is shocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want water?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.03,0:06:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your soup's different from the stuff in 18-liter tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not too sweet. It's just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.41,0:06:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see that you've been at this for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:06:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.71,0:07:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 250 yen per bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You normally have to pay up front.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.21,0:07:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're able to stay calm even after all that praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.67,0:07:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you avoid getting emotionally involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.67,0:07:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l don't mean this in a bad way,\Nbut if you have such good stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.85,0:07:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why do business here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.81,0:07:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.52,0:07:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If one's led a straight life and been\Nlucky enough to build a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one wouldh't be cooking soba here at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.28,0:07:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One also wouldn't be eating soba either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You from Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.33,0:07:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, though I haven't been there in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.62,0:07:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You a fugitive?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.75,0:07:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.67,0:07:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, since I've been at this for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.25,0:07:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your girlfriend? Or your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both, yet neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.46,0:07:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.63,0:07:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.30,0:08:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Street-side Soba Song"\NSinger / Yomota Inumaru
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.40,0:08:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After wandering for many moons,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sit here at a street-side counter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.92,0:08:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The worn out varnish suits the place well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.06,0:08:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has seen too much sweat and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.61,0:08:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were a typical core family in a city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.70,0:09:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking back now, we had a decent condo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father had large debts, kept busy paying\Nthem off, and felt burdened by his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.88,0:09:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother hated dealing with neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.42,0:09:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was full of conceit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.64,0:09:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always wanted to go out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.01,0:09:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was scared of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.43,0:09:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So day after day,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.48,0:09:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just leaned out from the balcony and listened\Nto the rustling sound of goldenrod.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.61,0:09:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.82,0:09:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for someone to bring chaos and destruction\Nto my unchangeably mundane life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.12,0:09:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did he come?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who wasn't supposed to be there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.87,0:09:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who wasn't supposed to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was dressed in sunshine yellow, like Canadian\Ngoldenrod, and showed up at our door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.39,0:10:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the day she came,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my family bid a farewell to its mundane yet peaceful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I have another?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.95,0:10:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And some tempura on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.70,0:10:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.99,0:10:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you believe it if, out of the blue, your granddaughter\Ncame to visit you from the near future?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A street-side soba vendor doesn't believe in sci-fi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.09,0:10:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't believe it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.68,0:10:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl travelled on a time machine from\Nthe near future to see her ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The grandfather and granddaughter, who were\Nthe same age, were not supposed to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.27,0:10:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't believe in such an idiotic premise,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.31,0:10:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even after I saw the five-pointed star on her ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.65,0:11:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, even if she proved to be a con artist\Nlike my mother said, it didn't matter to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Words like family and blood relationships\Nare mere concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.91,0:11:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought, "I can live with that innocent girl just by\Nadmitting that she's my own granddaughter."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.88,0:11:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I could think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.64,0:11:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was her cunning trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I lived with her under the same roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.28,0:11:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't make her my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.08,0:11:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was idiotic of me to underestimate the power of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.92,0:11:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, family and blood relationships are mere concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.71,0:12:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are relationships defined only by words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is precisely why a concept defined\Nby words can only be disproved by words!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.64,0:12:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I accepted her one-sided argument at the outset,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.27,0:12:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,either I could be her kind grandfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or I could call her a liar and kick her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were the only two choices I had!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.78,0:12:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She used her beauty to intrude into someone else's family,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.99,0:12:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and yet she kept herself from all the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.83,0:12:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how she did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a bad woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.04,0:12:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even though I knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.92,0:12:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or actually, because of that, my feelings\Nfor her kept growing stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.42,0:12:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.97,0:12:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father even robbed a bank for her sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.55,0:12:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother took extreme measures to uncover her identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.68,0:12:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But both were bound by her spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.77,0:13:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She always said the proper things,\Nespecially when it came to our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.69,0:13:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we had no way to refute her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.11,0:13:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My family slowly but surely became\Nthe family of her own imagining,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and walked the path of corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The purchase of a new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.71,0:13:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot pots day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.63,0:13:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the life of fugitives as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.84,0:13:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have a hot one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want an egg in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.51,0:13:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And add a rice ball, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chopsticks, noodle bowl, chives, hot peppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.70,0:13:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lost beast is biting into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.96,0:14:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the soup its tears? Or its sighs?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.01,0:14:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It yearns for the moon and feels bohemian.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.77,0:14:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This short life is like a street-side vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.78,0:14:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money and women are also like a street-side vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.41,0:14:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They undergo many chance encounters, talking about food,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.83,0:14:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but once they exit the store,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.25,0:14:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it all ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.93,0:15:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flying past the rolls of steam
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.78,0:15:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the yellow airship from that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the yellow airship from that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.60,0:15:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we woke up in that road-side restaurant\Nwhere the final act had unfolded,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.11,0:15:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she was long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.74,0:15:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no forewarning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.03,0:15:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No signs at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.83,0:16:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her disappearance seemed so quick that\Nwe couldn't believe she was really gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.67,0:16:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we anxiously awaited her return.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.50,0:16:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A day passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.38,0:16:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't even return in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.34,0:16:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when night fell, at about the time we\Ncould feel the chill from the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.10,0:16:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we finally realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she had vanished from our lives forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when we also realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she hadn't just disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.12,0:16:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but had abandoned us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.41,0:16:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We didn't choose her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She chose us, then abandoned us after judging\Nthat we were unworthy to be her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.84,0:16:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother once left the family over\Nthe issue of Maroko's intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.88,0:16:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my father didn't try to stop her from leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.68,0:17:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I abandoned my mother and\Nchose to elope with Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.02,0:17:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We betrayed each other, and felt guilty about each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we lost her, the last tie holding us together,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.98,0:17:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could no longer stay together as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The family was scattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.74,0:17:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She chose another family, just like she had in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.87,0:17:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the story of my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.38,0:17:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.88,0:17:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what what happened after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.56,0:17:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad went crazy and disappeared,\Nand his whereabouts are unknown to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.27,0:17:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom started a photo studio with her lover,\Nin an attempt to begin a second life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.49,0:17:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's currently serving a sentence in an extortion case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.53,0:17:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And as for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm travelling from soba shop to\Nsoba shop, still looking for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.29,0:18:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to catch her to pick a quarrel with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.42,0:18:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.30,0:18:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She made me go through all that, and I'm still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.76,0:18:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just remembering her face...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or mentioning her name...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.39,0:18:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gives me pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.73,0:18:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and warmth...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.66,0:18:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.57,0:18:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.99,0:18:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.33,0:18:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a pretty good story, but after thirty years\Nof experience at this, you can't trick me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.17,0:18:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.13,0:18:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit mumbling, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a pro at this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.97,0:19:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,known as Inumaru the Tragic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.89,0:19:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l'd heard of a young wanderer working this area recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.89,0:19:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you had the guts to show up at my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.11,0:19:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman con artist who claimed to be your\Ngranddaughter come from the near future?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.82,0:19:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta start a tall tale with a more believable premise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.95,0:19:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate the power of stories!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.21,0:19:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.05,0:19:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the rice ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.93,0:19:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'ya talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.14,0:19:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you dreaming about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dreaming?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyashirazu...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.23,0:20:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's lived in that condo since they\Nfound a design fault in the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.57,0:20:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.12,0:20:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.15,0:22:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.90,0:23:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma... ro... ko...
